-- S.Africa's stock market delays open on network problems
-- By Helen Nyambura-Mwaura
-- Mon Sep 15, 2014 03:39AM EDT
-- None



JOHANNESBURG, Sept 15 (Reuters) - South Africa's Johannesburg Stock Exchange was experiencing a network connectivity problem that had delayed the start of trade on Monday, it said in a statement, adding that this required a reboot of one of its trading switches.

